\begin_body

\begin_layout Standard
For this version, the context of use would be during a therapy session that
 is being realize in a sufficiently large space occupied by the child and
 the robot Teo2 with the therapist as an external observer that limits to
 control Teo, in case that is neccesary –such in a situation in which a
 collision must be avoided, make it re-explain the dynamic, etc–, and to
 complement the reinformance and the guidance to the child.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subparagraph
Goal
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The goal of the game is provide a controlled setting in which Teo and the
 child can interact with a limited set of possibilities.
 In this way, the child can learn to be comfortable with Teo.
 Moreover, the game intends for the child to understand the dynamic of the
 game and follow it to its conclusion.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subparagraph
Interface
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The therapist has access to the computer application 
\shape italic

\begin_inset Quotes fld
\end_inset

Teo2Control
\begin_inset Quotes frd
\end_inset


\shape default
 in which she chooses 
\shape italic
Marcopolo game - version 1
\shape default
, to start its execution.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subparagraph
Dynamic of the game
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The child and Teo share sufficiently large space to move around, in principle,
 a space greater or equal to 25 squared meters.
 After the selection of the Marcopolo execution by the therapist, the game
 starts with a 
\begin_inset Quotes fld
\end_inset

blindfolded
\begin_inset Quotes frd
\end_inset

 Teo, which explains to the child that it cannot see him and that he must
 move further from him as he can.
 Also, Teo explains that whenever it needs help to find him (the child),
 it will call out 
\begin_inset Quotes fld
\end_inset

Where are you?
\begin_inset Quotes frd
\end_inset

 and that he (the child) must answer out loud 
\begin_inset Quotes fld
\end_inset

Teo, here!
\begin_inset Quotes frd
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

